        better late than never - brat is finally a number 1 album!! and with the remix album helping it get there, ill share my thoughts on that.

        firstly, lets state the obvious. the 365 remix with shygirl is finally out, and ive yearned for this since june, its one of the most adrenaline-fueled things to come from this year. that drop is insane. the only gripe i have with it is that its too short - eight more bars and a not-so-abrupt ending on the final drop would have put it on par with the original for me. but as it stands, FANTASTIC song.

        sympathy is a knife with ariana was a big surprise - like billie, i didnt know how shed fit on it, but she absolutely kills it here, complete with a little bit of filthiness in the outro that really sold it for me. everything is romantic is a more lofi version of the original, but its still great - and if you havent already, please check out carolines album from last year, its fantastic. i might say something stupid is better than the original; it starts as an ambient piece, but gradually turns into a crescendoing indie-rock ballad and its just beautiful. club classics is the most underground-sounding song here, utilising a garage beat, a great verse from bb trickz (who i never heard of before this), and a pinch of 365. and this might be a hot take but i prefer the remixes of rewind, apple and b2b too!

        the only remixes that i felt were duds on this thing were von dutch, which doesnt carry as much oomph as the original, and i found addison rae to be quite obnoxious on the track, and mean girls, which really didnt need to be slowed-down and with a different beat. the latter is one of those songs where she should have stuck to the original beat, like she did on 360, guess, spring breakers and girl so confusing (top 3 on the remix album btw!)

        overall, even if i think the original is really hard to beat, charli still assembled a great remix album, but this project really depends on what you enjoyed the most about brat. but even then, more brat was just what we needed
